reviews.text: As junior high students people within our age group gathered as many as 100 kids all summer long, skating, biking, frisbee, or just went to see who was around since we had no CELLPHONES!!
Somewhat unique among capitol buildings in the United States with its high-rise design, the grounds are still very attractive and the capitol stately.
The views from the 18th storey are breathtaking.
Beautiful campus.
I love going to the capitol grounds.  Its so beautiful and the buildings have so much history.  As a photographer you can always find something beautiful to capture!
Great place, too bad its only open once a year
Buckstop Junction itself is charming. If you can get the Saturday tour, go for it. Apple fest itself, meh for grownups.

Buckstop Junction is a nice little "slice of history" on the edge of Bismarck, North Dakota. It has old, historic buildings in a rustic late 19th or early 20th century setting. It is a nice place for gatherings like family reunions or weddings.
Love Applefest! A wonderful family weekend!
Cool histotic ppace for gatherings

This is a really cool scenic overlook. There are small trailers with detailed information about the Native Americans that inhabited the area. If you looking for a peaceful place to enjoy a good view, this spot should be on your list.
It has an interesting history and a fabulous view. The park has lots of information kiosks to learn about the place.
Great place to go for a walk
A nice overlook of Bismarck
Come for the scenic views and stay for the Legendary Raids!

The area is clean, easy to navigate, and beautiful. There are plaques detailing the history about the site, and are very interesting to read. It's a medium sized walking area, and is good for a quick stop to soak in some scenery. The sun sets on the other side of the river, and can be viewed very well from here. There are benches to sit on as well. If you are passing through, I would recommend stopping here for a quick stroll.
I love coming to this place especially in the spring and fall there is a presence here

A fascinating historic and archaeological site situated on a bluff overlooking the Missouri River.  I suggest visiting the ND Heritage Center first to see their Double Ditch mural.  This will help you become familiar with how life was like in this Mandan Indian village in its heyday.  Then go to the real site, and with its silent stillness, let the past come alive in your imagination.
Nice view of river. Gives a sense of the life on these river bluffs. Not much for kids but has historical boards to read. Pretty country. Nice place for a small picnic.
This place used to be good, until tons of people started coming here.
This Santa was wonderful. Spent real time talking with the children and nice tour of the historic governor mansion.
Well managed. Let you have the run of the place, see all the neat hideaways.
Amazing house, so cool that you can just freely walk around and take your time. Definitely a must if you like history and old houses.
It was interesting to see the inside of a old beautiful building that used to house our state governors.

This a really cool place with detailed history about the governors of ND. The wormwood is beautiful. Seeing the different wallpapers of past decades will be interesting. Do not forget to check out the carriage house!

Very nice museum detailing the rich history of the area. It has many sections. These include a prehistoric section with skeletons of many extinct creatures. A section about the Amerindians and their way of life. A section on the history of North Dakota itself and how it came to be. It also includes important information on what it produces. The gift shop is a nice place to get postcards and other cool little souvenirs. If you are ever stopping through North Dakota, this is definitely a place to put on your list to see!
Whole family has fun when we go. We notice different things every time. The kids love the interactive pieces and the treehouse. Definitely a must see if you're going through Bismarck.

We visited on a Sunday morning, everyone we talked with was very friendly! Our kids loved the exhibits and spent almost 45 min playing in the treehouse. There are many new exhibits since I was a kid. I would suggest at least 3 hours to see all of the new stuff if you haven't been there in a while. The gift shop isn't cheap but it has many fun items in it.

We like to bring the kids here. They have a lot fun. Plus, they may inadvertently learn something. The new Tree House play area is a great addition for little kids. Much cooler than the old jail house and wooden horses we played on when were young.

We love to visit this place. Every time we visit Bismarck,, our young children beg us to take them there to learn the history. How can we say no to have them learn about the past . Next your in Bismarck make sure you stop by this museum. It’s free and very educational

The service leaves something to be desired. 
Mainly service. 
I assume they all share one cerebral cortex. 
Nobody cared whether or not I was there to being with .
I was served water that had been passed through a dirty coffee filter. 
When I told her that I needed actual coffee, she proceeded to fill the glass again with what I can only call poor man's tea.
I are the 2 biscuits on my plate because they were edible.
My server waddled into the sunset never to be seen again I left my 12$ on the counter.

You can have my coffee since u think it's so good. I'm tired. I'm going to get a red bull. 
Thank u for wasting my time.

We had a lovely Valentine's day date! Our server, Brittany was delightful! Very informative about the questions I had and very nice! She checked in often enough to ensure we had everything we wanted, but not so often that we felt bothered. Over all ot was a wonderful experience! Plus the food is awesome!
I just stopped in for dessert but the service was great. Nice and  clean and fast. The banana split was good and even though I know its work to make it, the server was very nice.
Was there for breakfast. Great friendly service. Great food
Awesome is all we can say. Real authentic food.

The price is good for what you get....the burgers are really some of the best in the area. Its also very clean for being a busy place so that was impressive, im not a big fan of sports places but if the food and service is good then its fine with me. The waitress was great, her name was Lexi and she was very good at her job! and you don't see that much lately in places.  We will be back! Thanks!

Great burgers, the cheese curds are amazing and there's an ever changing selection of craft beers on tap.  Not your typical sports bar : Reza's got an upscale environment with a relaxed atmosphere.  Prices are reasonable too!

My wife and I stopped in at 3:00pm today to have a meal after running errands. We had been here before and had an expectation of quality service. Unfortunately, we were about to be disappointed. After seating ourselves, we waited over 10 minutes and were not greeted or served by the waitstaff. During that time, we sat at the table, wondering if anyone would notice the exasperated look on our faces, lack of drinks or filled out order tickets. Nothing. So we tore up our tickets to send the message that we wouldn't tolerate such terrible service and went home. This establishment didn't our receive our money today and will never get our patronage again. I will make it my goal to tell all of my friends and family about this experience.
Good local burger joint.  It has beer and is thought of as a sports bar but it is some place i can take my younger son.  He enjoys the foosball table.
This was one of the most expensive burgers I've ever eaten. Good, but not $12 good. I doubt I will be going back.

The atmosphere and service is wonderful! Its a fantastic location and looks like a fun place to visit. However, the food was lacking in flavor, unfortunately. They have the location and atmosphere, just not the food.

Food was cold and just bland tasting food. Never will my wife and I go back there. Unless they revamp everything there. They only have good drinks and should make it a bar/pub or something. Mexican food is not what they're serving! Lol

I used to live here and this was the place to be and eat for Mexican food, and the house margaritas...THE BEST!  I just went there tonight, in town again for business and again very good service and food.  Perhaps the othere reviews were on Friday and Sat nights when it's packed... Not sure why such bad remarks, by far my favorate place in Bismarck. Thanks Fiesta! Can't wait to be in town again.

This place was pretty bad. Thwreath we're only 5 people I the whole place and the service was pretty slow. The rice was just inedible I have no idea how they could make it like that. The taco bar was pretty stale and old. The salsa bland. The chips they brought to the table were old.  We r pretty dissapointed and will never be back.

Nice looking but that's it. How can you be a Mexican restaurant and not have horchata? 

I ordered a steak torta, easy right? Never had one so off point.

My brother works here so since he started working here my boyfriend and I have decided to come a little more to see him and also enjoy a meal. The service here is wonderfully fantastic and service is 100% perfect and I wouldn’t change anything about this place and now the rest of the family loves this place too. This is now our new number 1 eating place it may be a little pricey but it’s worth the price!
Friendly staff, good food, good price for a all you can eat stir fry place. Kind of busy but the line moved fast. Waitresses are attainative.
Really expensive considering you make your own food. I could be wrong but, I feel like if I'm going to pay to eat somewhere, they should prepare the food for me. I can make my own food at home.

We love huhot! takes a while to figure out what the best combination is, because they have so many choices.

We have always been seated quickly and treated well by staff. They do a fantastic job of keeping the floor and cooking area clean through the messy cooking process.

Sometimes we get rogue ingredients due to the grill, so if you have allergies they will put up a barrier to prevent allergens.

They also have one of those flavor-fancy soda machines so you can get a new soda flavor everytime you come (raspberry is great!).

Always very good food but the employees are extremely rude. The hostess and one of servers were rude, the hostess rolled her eyes and was agitated when I walked by. Management needs to teach their crew about manners and not acting like customers are a hassle.
One of my favorite places in Bismarck. Always an amazing experience. Top notch service. Great food. I always recommend this place.

Came with my special lady... ordered a beer and her a foo foo drink. Manager was bartender at this time. This was due to my timing, arriving between lunch and dinner. Still great service, just enough, and the food was delicious. Had the lobster bisque and lobster and 4 cheese ravioli, was very good and creamy. Just like it should be... 😉 good job guys, keep it up, and I’ll be back!
Upscale restaurant with great food, and friendly service. Also has a nice bar attached with outdoor seating for the beautiful summer evenings.

This was my first visit here. It was a great experience, the service was impeccable I don't think I've ever had better service!!! And the food was perfect! I had lobster ravioli and it had generous portions of lobster and decadent four cheese ravioli! I will definitely be returning!!

The Bistro offers a unique fine dining experience or just a great atmosphere to have a glass of wine and spend time with friends. The owners are amazing members of the community with giving hearts to those needing a bit of help.

Wonderful food and vibe. Excellent lunch specials. Sometimes, dinner wait can be unusually long. Last time, we waited 15 minutes at our table before we could finally get someone to take our water order. Recommend going for lunch or on slower nights. The food quality seems to suffer on busy nights.

We went to Kobe’s and we had the best food we have ever ordered I really recommend this Steakhouse to other visitors. 5 Stars Went for lunch with myfriend. He ordered a specialty sushi roll while I ordered the tempura shrimp lunchbox. Both did not disappoint! The lunchbox had large portions and a variety of items, very reasonably priced. The sushi roll was also delicious! Will come back again soon!

Great spot. It was busy. We had a ten minute wait which isn't that bad. However, the food took too long, especially considering that both of us only ordered sushi for our meal, which must be prepared, but not cooked. So we were both wondering what the holdup was. That being said, it was very good food.

Very nice food displays. The food tastes great as well. Great service. Everyone there had a genuine smile (as if they really liked their job or striving to please the customers). Wonderful atmosphere. I love the dim lights. Pretty classy. The location of this place is perfect. It is Not far from the freeway and next to a decent size shopping location. Pretty easy to see from the street as well. The parking is pretty good for a very popular place. I will be back for more soon.
Kobe's has been a great place to go every single time I've visited.  Courteous hosts and servers every time.  Delicious fresh food.  Honestly, I've never had a bad experience ever!
